assessment_details.task_description:
Active engagement is a key part of learning in this course. Students are required to read and engage with readings and skill builders discussing contemporary performance management problems faced in organisations. Engagement and facilitation is evidenced through the following activities:

leadership role for facilitation of small group discussion for TWO scheduled topics and TWO scheduled Skill-Builders;

active engagement with all assigned readings through reading and commenting on online discussion forums;

engagement with all assigned readings through participation in discussions and debates held in seminar sessions;

engagement with all scheduled Skill-Builders and Workshops through participation in exercises and activities held in seminar sessions; and

active engagement with facilitated discussions through posting follow up and take-away notes on online discussion forums.

See course handouts for detailed assessment information.
